name: I Love Rock 'N Roll 11 x 17 Print
description:
My kids were the genius' behind this print. They came up with this lyric swap to the famous "I Love Rock 'N Roll" song by Joan Jett, which we quite often rock out to. You should have heard their rolling laughter when they discovered the cleverness of their word swap and that it actually worked with the song! Of course dime and jukebox mean nothing to a 5 and a 3 year old...but straw and juicebox sure do! 

Perfect print for the little rocker in your life! Or juicebox addict..whatever. Comes in an array of colors too. Hand drawn in Illustrator.

Have a specific color combo in mind that you don't see? Contact me! For just $10 more I will be happy to create a custom color combo for you. 

{Details}
:: 11 x 17 inches
:: Printed with an Epson 1400 using archival inks
:: Printed on Ultra Premium Presentation Matte Photo Paper for Epson
:: Frame and Matte not included

{Note}
:: Print ships FLAT and will be carefully packaged in a recycled kraft sturdy mailer.
:: Print ships Parcel Post because of it's size. Shipping is usually 2-9 days. If you need it expedited please convo me before purchasing.

Frame and Mat not included.

©2011 ec design & illustration

name: Put the Kettle On 8 x 10 Giclee Print
description:
This is an 8 x 10 archival inkjet print of an illustrated page from my Moleskine for The Sketchbook Project depicting my favorite time(s) of day - tea time and coffee time! My theme was 'A Day in The Life'. My original spread is pictured in the last photo. It was originally done in black ink and it has been digitally colored for this print. My Sketchbook is now in Art House Co-op's permanent collection at the Brooklyn Art Library.
